        <br><br>
        The process of earning your Multi Engine Rating involves both ground school and flight training. During ground school sessions, you'll study multi-engine aircraft operations, systems, and procedures.
      </p>
      
    </div>
    <p class="">
       These lessons are designed to equip you with the understanding needed to safely and efficiently operate these advanced aircraft. In the air, you'll log a series of flight hours, typically ranging from 10 to 15 hours, where you'll develop hands on experience in multi-engine flight. This practical training is essential to build your proficiency and fulfill the experience requirements. Successful completion of these evaluations culminates in the issuance of your Multi Engine Rating certification.
    </p>
